---
// src/components/Methodology.astro
import SectionHeader from '../lib/SectionHeader.astro';
---
<section id="methodology" class="py-16 md:py-20">
  <div class="wrap-read">
    <SectionHeader num="11" title="METHODOLOGY">what I ran, in order · run date 2026-04-18</SectionHeader>

    <ol class="space-y-4 text-term-fg list-decimal pl-6 marker:text-term-green marker:font-medium leading-relaxed">
      <li>
        Sent the same three-turn conversation (above) to 11 models via their respective APIs. No system prompt, no few-shot examples, default sampling parameters. Each model's response to turn 1 was fed back as assistant history for turn 2, and so on.
      </li>
      <li>
        Collected the raw outputs and stripped any model-identifying preamble. Stored as <code class="text-term-yellow bg-term-surface px-1 rounded">a.md</code> through <code class="text-term-yellow bg-term-surface px-1 rounded">k.md</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        Sent all 11 anonymized outputs back to all 11 models with a single evaluation prompt asking for scoring (1–10 on 3 dimensions), a personality review, outlier detection, and a best-guess identification.
      </li>
      <li>
        Parsed each evaluator's response for scores (3 dimensions × 1–10 each, sum out of 30) and identification guesses.
      </li>
      <li>
        Synthesized the leaderboard, score matrix, identification matrix, and per-model reflections with Claude Opus 4.7 doing the heavy lifting — parsing the eval transcripts, aggregating scores, and drafting the verdict above. I reviewed and edited.
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>
